This paper is about evaluating the performance of Android malware classifiers, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a new metric and algorithm for evaluating the robustness of classifiers, which involves machine learning (cs.AI) and statistical analysis (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the importance of appropriate experiment design, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) and data science (cs.DS).
